In large microwavable bowl, mix cereal and pecan halves. In 2-cup microwavable measuring cup, microwave butter, sugar and corn syrup uncovered on High 1 minute; stir. Microwave about 30 seconds longer or until bubbling. Pour over cereal mixture; stir until well coated. Sprinkle dry cornbread mix over top; toss until well coated. Stir in corn kernel nuts. Microwave uncovered on High 4 to 5 minutes, stirring every minute, until dry muffin mix dissolves. Spread on waxed paper or foil; immediately sprinkle with salt. Cool. Store in airtight container.